Fresh-branch enrichment for `GET /experimental/workspace`.

Reads `.git/HEAD` per row at list time and overrides
WorkspaceTable.branch in the response so `kfactory list` can show a
live branch column. The kfactory-adapter never populates the stored
branch column (it doesn't track checkout state), so without this
patch the workspace.list response always returns branch=null.

Implementation:
  - `readBranchFromGitHead(directory)` parses `ref: refs/heads/<X>`
    from `.git/HEAD`. Detached HEAD or missing .git -> undefined.
  - `WorkspaceHttpApi.list` resolves branches via Effect.forEach
    with concurrency: "unbounded", each row's read wrapped in
    Effect.sync. fs.readFileSync is fine here -- the file is at most
    one disk seek per row.
  - Response shape unchanged: `branch` field was already in
    Workspace.Info (just always null for kfactory-adapter dispatches).

Stacking: applies AFTER `opencode-bearer-and-routing` and BEFORE
`opencode-session-subscribers`. Touches only handlers/workspace.ts,
which neither neighbour modifies, so the stack is order-independent
in practice.

